str2: Then, thereafter, afterwards. From epi and eita; thereafter.
Three. Or neuter tria a primary number; 'three'.
A year. Apparently a primary word; a year.

parse: Verb - Aorist Indicative Active - 1st Person Singular
str2: To come up, go up, ascend. From ana and erchomai; to ascend.
A primary preposition; to or into, of place, time, or purpose; also in adverbial phrases.
The Greek form of the Hebrew name: Jerusalem. Of Hebrew origin; Hierosolyma
To get acquainted with, visit. From a derivative of eido; to be knowing, i.e. to visit for information.
Of Chaldee origin; the Rock; Cephas, a surname of Peter.

parse: Verb - Aorist Indicative Active - 1st Person Singular
str2: (a) I remain, tarry, (b) I remain in, persist in. From epi and meno; to stay over, i.e. Remain.
To, towards, with. A strengthened form of pro; a preposition of direction; forward to, i.e. Toward.

parse: Personal / Possessive Pronoun - Accusative Masculine 3rd Person Singular
str2: He, she, it, they, them, same. From the particle au; the reflexive pronoun self, used of the third person, and of the other persons.
Fifteen. From deka and pente; ten and five, i.e. Fifteen.
A day, the period from sunrise to sunset.
